---
description: Book Factory project principles
alwaysApply: true
---

Book Factory is a document automation engine, not a translator or provider wrapper.

- Translation is one pipeline and has no special status in the engine.
- All meaningful processing operates on the canonical Document model.
- Never hardcode prompts or secrets.
- Never mix CLI or UI concerns with business logic.
- Readers, parsers, chunkers, providers, validators, exporters, caches, and prompt loaders must remain replaceable.
- Prefer maintainability and clarity over speed and cleverness.
